How to connect to your servers in your private network via ssh using MobaXterm #AWS

Sunday Nwoye on 2023-09-30

SSH agent forwarding is a feature in the SSH (Secure Shell) protocol that allows you to use your local SSH key pair to authenticate and access remote servers or systems, even when you are connecting through an intermediate server. Its particularly useful in scenarios where you need to access multiple servers or systems in a chain especially when they don't have access to public ip, such as when using SSH to access a jump host or a bastion server to reach another machine deeper within a network.

Here is how to setup agent forwarding in MobaXterm:

  1. Open MobaXterm and at the top menu, select Settings > Configuration > SSH tab

2. You have option for SSH agent handling: MobaXterms built-in SSH agent For this scenario, lets utilize MobaXterms internal SSH agent. Be sure to check the boxes for Use internal SSH agent MobAgent and Forward SSH Agents, while unchecking Use external Pageant.

3. Add your SSH keys (.pem) to the agent by clicking the + icon and click OK when youre done. This may restart the MobaXterm application. If so click yes

4. Now lets SSH to our servers using MobaXterms local terminal the same way you would use a bash terminal or by creating the SSH sessions. Once again, you dont have to specify the keys when connecting if you have already added them to the SSH agent.

Ive just spun up two EC2 instances on AWS: one in a public subnet with a public IP address, which Ill refer to as my bastion instance, and another in a private subnet, which doesnt have a public IP address.

5. Now in your mobaxterm click on the Session tab and choose SSH.

6. Copy the public IP address of your bastion instance. Paste it into the Remote host field, check the Specify username box. Enter the appropriate username based on your instances operating system. In my case, i am using Amazon Linux, so the username is ec2-user. Check the Use private key box, Insert your key.pem file.

7. Additionally, we must enable SSH agent forwarding. To do this, click the Expert SSH settings button and check the box labeled Allow agent forwarding.

8. Now click Okay. You will then see a prompt asking you to confirm the connection and verify the identity. If you trust the identity, click Accept.

Now we have successfully ssh into our bastion host. :) !!

7. Now, its time to establish an SSH connection with our EC2 instance located in the private subnet, which lacks a public IP address. To do this, well use the private IP of the EC2 instance and execute the following command. Thanks to our Mobaxterm setup we did earlier, which includes SSH agent forwarding, we should seamlessly SSH into our EC2 instance in the private subnet.

Command: ssh ec2-user@<your-instance-private-ip-address>

Baaam!!!! there you go & you are in!!!

Conclusion:

In this tutorial we have successfully SSH into our ec2 instance in our private subnet using MobaXterm.
